               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16901210-24-off123-c89" targOrder="Y" targets="t16901210-24-defend131 t16901210-24-off123 t16901210-24-verdict126"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16901210-24-defend131" type="defendantName">
                     Peter 
                     Hesey
                  <interp inst="t16901210-24-defend131" type="surname" value="Hesey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-defend131" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-defend131" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was tryed for <rs id="t16901210-24-off123" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-off123" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-off123" type="offenceSubcategory" value="burglary"></interp>
               breaking the House of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16901210-24-victim133" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Clements
                        <interp inst="t16901210-24-victim133" type="surname" value="Clements"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16901210-24-victim133" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16901210-24-victim133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16901210-24-off123 t16901210-24-victim133"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , of the Parish of <placeName id="t16901210-24-crimeloc124">S. Leonard's Foster-lane</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-crimeloc124" type="placeName" value="S. Leonard's Foster-lane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-crimeloc124" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16901210-24-off123 t16901210-24-crimeloc124"></join>, on <rs id="t16901210-24-cd125" type="crimeDate">November 4</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16901210-24-off123 t16901210-24-cd125"></join>
               
                  </rs>. The Evidence was, That five suspicious Persons being discovered by a Neighbour to hanker about the House at an unseasonable hour, he and a Watchman so well observed them, that some runing off, as perceiving they were discovered, the 5th, viz. the Prisoner was found under the Window, which he had broken open, and a not pursuit made after him, he was taken with the prosecutor's Cane in his Hand; and it appearing the House had been entred, Goods taken out and removed, &amp;c. and he giving no satisfactory account of himself was found <rs id="t16901210-24-verdict126" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-verdict126" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs> of Felony and Burglary.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16901210-24-punish127" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16901210-24-punish127" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16901210-24-defend131 t16901210-24-punish127"></join>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
